animal /ˈænɪməl/

(animals) 

1. N-COUNT An animal is a living creature such as a dog, lion, or rabbit, rather than a bird, fish, insect, or human being. 动物 (不包括鸟类、鱼类、昆虫和人类) 

例： He was attacked by wild animals. 他被野兽袭击了。 

2. N-COUNT Any living creature other than a human being can be referred to as an animal . 兽类; 动物 (不包括人类) 

例： Language is something that fundamentally distinguishes humans from animals. 语言是从根本上把人类与动物区分开的事物。 

3. N-COUNT Any living creature, including a human being, can be referred to as an animal . (包括人类在内的) 动物 

例： Watch any young human being, or any other young animal. 观察任意一个年少的人，或者任意其他幼小的动物。 

4. ADJ Animal products come from animals rather than from plants. 动物的 

例： ...food high in animal fats such as red meat and dairy products. …富含动物脂肪的食物，如红色肉类和奶制品。

